  // By default try to get ID from the query arguments: getStudent(id: ID!)
  // If that is empty then try to use the value from the @source directive
  // in the schema definition.  This allows us to use the same resolver
  // from a query (getUser(id)) or from a nested field (getIncident/assignedTo)
  var sysId = env.getArguments().id || env.getSource();

  gr.query("sys_id", sysId);

  return gr;
})(env);

}

	id: String @source(value: "sys_id.value")

	state: String! @source(value: "state.display_value")

}

type Manufacturer {

	name: String @source(value: "name.value")

}

type Model {
	id: String @source(value: "sys_id.value")
	modelName : String @source(value: "model_name.value")
	type: String @source(value: "type.value")
	manufacturer: Manufacturer @source(value: "manufacturer.value")

	year: Int @source(value: "year.value")

type Part {

}

    {
        "name": "vehicleGQL",
        "label": "Vehicle GraphQL Response",
        "readOnly": false,
        "fieldType": "JSON",
        "mandatory": true,
        "defaultValue": ""
      }
]</props><required_translations>[ {
  "message" : "Vehicle GraphQL Response",
  "comment" : ""
} ]</required_translations><schema_version>1.0.0</schema_version><script><![CDATA[function transform(input) {
	var vehicleObj = input.vehicleGQL.data.xSncFltMgmt.fleet.vehicle;
	var newVehicleObj = {
		"vehicleMetadata": {
			"sysID": vehicleObj.id,
			"number": vehicleObj.number,
			"model": vehicleObj.model.modelName,
			"image": vehicleObj.image
		},
		"vehicleInfo": [
			{"label": "License plate: ", "value": vehicleObj.licensePlate},
			{"label": "VIN: ", "value": vehicleObj.vin},
			{"label": "Next oil change: ", "value": vehicleObj.oilChange},
			{"label": "Next tire rotation: ", "value": vehicleObj.tireRotation}
		],
		"maintReqs": vehicleObj.maintReqs,
		"parts": vehicleObj.parts
	};
	return newVehicleObj;
}]]></script><sys_class_name>sys_ux_data_broker_scriptlet</sys_class_name><sys_created_by>admin</sys_created_by><sys_created_on>2022-08-23 17:09:55</sys_created_on><sys_id>a1727c3087ad9550bf924085dabb350b</sys_id><sys_mod_count>3</sys_mod_count><sys_name>Vehicle Scriptlet Transform</sys_name><sys_package display_value="Fleet Vehicle Management" source="x_snc_flt_mgmt">89b467169738d150c6fc7e0e6253af10</sys_package><sys_policy/><sys_scope display_value="Fleet Vehicle Management">89b467169738d150c6fc7e0e6253af10</sys_scope><sys_update_name>sys_ux_data_broker_scriptlet_a1727c3087ad9550bf924085dabb350b</sys_update_name><sys_updated_by>admin</sys_updated_by><sys_updated_on>2022-08-24 03:14:49</sys_updated_on></sys_ux_data_broker_scriptlet><sys_translated_text action="delete_multiple" query="documentkey=a1727c3087ad9550bf924085dabb350b"/></record_update>

    {
        "name": "vehicleSysId",
        "label": "Vehicle SysID",
        "readOnly": false,
        "fieldType": "string",
        "mandatory": true,
        "defaultValue": ""
      }
]</props><query>query ($vehicleSysId: ID!) {
    xSncFltMgmt {
        fleet {
            vehicle(id: $vehicleSysId) {
                maintReqs {
                    id
                    number
                    shortDescription
                    assignedTo {
                        id
                        name
                    }
                    maintTasks {
                        id
                        number
                        shortDescription
                        assignedTo {
                            id
                            name
                        }
                    }
                }
                parts {
                    serialNumber
                    partName
                }
            }
        }
    }
}</query><required_translations>[ {
